[It is difficult to know what caused this cluster of cases. It is not clear if all were diagnosed with encephalitis or not, nor is the cause of the disease mentioned. If it is a cluster of encephalitis cases, it is too early in the season for Japanese encephalitis virus or enterovirus infections. They usually occur in northeastern India and Bangladesh June through October. Encephalitis from Nipah virus infections is well known in Bangladesh, occurs during the same season as these cases, but was not mentioned as a possible cause. ProMED would appreciate receiving additional information about these cases and any new ones that might occur. - Mod.TY

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1yvE.]

